WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.135 --> 00:00:06.505
<i>Carroll was convicted in 2004 for
the murders of 14 young women...</i>

2
00:00:06.673 --> 00:00:09.575
I have so many
surprises waiting for you.

3
00:00:10.043 --> 00:00:12.308
- Tell me who Roderick is.
- A friend of Joe's.

4
00:00:12.479 --> 00:00:15.559
- What's Joe doing? Why do you listen him?
- He's teaching me to feel my life.

5
00:00:16.383 --> 00:00:17.442
Damn it!

6
00:00:17.618 --> 00:00:20.213
Federal agents. Get down. now!
- Aah!

7
00:00:20.387 --> 00:00:22.879
- I was supposed to bring your mom here.
- What happened?

8
00:00:23.056 --> 00:00:25.548
I screwed up. What
happened to Paul and Jacob?

9
00:00:25.726 --> 00:00:27.558
Why did you leave us? Emma!

10
00:00:27.728 --> 00:00:30.892
The warden granted Carroll's
request for a transfer. He's leaving.

11
00:00:31.064 --> 00:00:33.693
Joe's not in the vehicle.
His people got to the warden.

12
00:00:33.867 --> 00:00:34.926
Where is he?

13
00:00:35.102 --> 00:00:36.382
I'm David. It's a pleasure. sir.

14
00:00:41.308 --> 00:00:43.277
So Joe's free.
Now I get locked up.

15
00:00:43.443 --> 00:00:45.571
Protective custody.
Better if I don't know.

16
00:00:45.746 --> 00:00:49.547
- Hey. Joey.
- I know you. You're my dad.

17
00:00:58.959 --> 00:01:00.689
Don't worry.

18
00:01:01.261 --> 00:01:02.854
Hey. good morning.

19
00:01:03.397 --> 00:01:05.195
Did you sleep all right?

20
00:01:07.200 --> 00:01:09.101
I know you're scared of me.

21
00:01:10.070 --> 00:01:13.768
I sensed it last night
when I first arrived.

22
00:01:15.075 --> 00:01:19.479
But I hope that will change and
you'll give me another chance.

23
00:01:23.917 --> 00:01:27.081
Nothing? Don't
want to speak to me?

24
00:01:28.989 --> 00:01:30.787
Well. that's okay.

25
00:01:31.425 --> 00:01:34.327
Look. I'm sorry your mother
isn't here. She was meant to be.

26
00:01:34.494 --> 00:01:39.262
That was the plan. But then
things went a little. pfft. awry.

27
00:01:39.466 --> 00:01:42.732
I am doing everything
I can to rectify that.

28
00:01:42.903 --> 00:01:46.101
But. uh. in the meantime.
I hope that you will. ah...

29
00:01:46.406 --> 00:01:51.777
You'll give me a chance to prove
that I am not a horrible man...

30
00:01:51.945 --> 00:01:55.074
and I have the
ability to be a rather...

31
00:01:55.415 --> 00:01:59.284
cool and fun guy... Dad.

32
00:02:00.454 --> 00:02:02.013
Dad.

33
00:02:06.760 --> 00:02:09.924
Look. we'll. um. take
things slow. huh?

34
00:02:12.532 --> 00:02:14.592
Well. that's all for now. uh...

35
00:02:26.413 --> 00:02:27.437
How'd it go?

36
00:02:28.181 --> 00:02:31.310
He's giving me
the silent treatment.

37
00:02:32.419 --> 00:02:34.854
He needs to get to
know you. That's all.

38
00:02:37.524 --> 00:02:41.222
- Come. everyone's waiting.
- What for?

39
00:02:42.462 --> 00:02:43.987
For you.

40
00:03:11.024 --> 00:03:13.255
Good morning. everybody.

41
00:03:22.102 --> 00:03:26.563
A suspect instrumental in Carroll's
escape was wounded and taken into custody.

42
00:03:26.740 --> 00:03:29.904
<i>Several deaths have already
been attributed to the escaped killer.</i>

43
00:03:30.077 --> 00:03:32.012
<i>One victim is
Carroll's attorney...</i>

44
00:03:32.179 --> 00:03:35.240
Carroll has escaped twice. This
time he flew away in a helicopter.

45
00:03:35.482 --> 00:03:39.510
There's no way to spin that. This
is a Bureau nightmare. people.

46
00:03:39.720 --> 00:03:41.518
From now on. we
have a new protocol.

47
00:03:41.722 --> 00:03:44.248
All investigations will
need to be approved by me.

48
00:03:44.424 --> 00:03:47.292
I apologize in advance
for being a control freak.

49
00:03:47.461 --> 00:03:48.821
That's the way
we're doing things.

50
00:03:51.331 --> 00:03:53.027
So I see Quantico
sent in a new guy.

51
00:03:53.200 --> 00:03:55.135
Nick Donovan. top
of the food chain.

52
00:03:55.302 --> 00:03:58.136
Director Franklin brought
him in to supervise us.

53
00:03:58.305 --> 00:04:00.399
So it's official. The
Bureau's freaking out.

54
00:04:00.607 --> 00:04:03.304
Everyone is freaking out.
Ryan. Carroll escaped twice.

55
00:04:03.510 --> 00:04:05.638
Have you turned on the
TV? The news is insane.

56
00:04:05.812 --> 00:04:08.577
What about Claire? Is she
safe? Has anyone spoken to her?

57
00:04:08.749 --> 00:04:10.911
- Who's got her detail? Turner?
- I don't know.

58
00:04:11.084 --> 00:04:13.576
She's in protective custody.
I don't have clearance.

59
00:04:13.754 --> 00:04:16.121
The guy in custody. the
acolyte from Joe's escape.

60
00:04:16.289 --> 00:04:19.259
- I need to question him. NICK:
You mean the one you tortured?

61
00:04:20.527 --> 00:04:22.792
- I got information.
- He did.

62
00:04:22.963 --> 00:04:26.297
We found the warden's daughter
and she is safe as a result.

63
00:04:28.635 --> 00:04:30.467
Ryan. nice to meet you.

64
00:04:32.539 --> 00:04:34.303
- Have we run prints on the guy?
- Yeah.

65
00:04:34.474 --> 00:04:38.605
We got nothing. This cult is doing a
good job of wiping their identities clean.

66
00:04:38.812 --> 00:04:42.579
We need to speak to him to find out
who and where this Roderick guy is.

67
00:04:42.749 --> 00:04:45.116
Ryan. we appreciate your help.

68
00:04:45.285 --> 00:04:48.278
But you were brought in as a
consultant. It's time you adopt...

69
00:04:48.488 --> 00:04:50.821
- a consulting presence.
- Carroll is the one...

70
00:04:50.991 --> 00:04:53.586
- who made Ryan more than a consultant.
- I'm aware.

71
00:04:53.760 --> 00:04:56.161
But Ryan is no longer
an agent with the FBI.

72
00:04:56.329 --> 00:05:00.425
- Oh. come on. you know as well as I...
- No. it's okay. He's right.

73
00:05:01.268 --> 00:05:02.292
I'm here to consult.

74
00:05:03.136 --> 00:05:06.129
This has become a Bureau
nightmare. right? I'm a liability.

75
00:05:06.773 --> 00:05:09.436
I'll just. uh... I'll be
in the other room.

76
00:05:10.177 --> 00:05:11.805
Consulting.

77
00:05:21.388 --> 00:05:24.119
- Everything okay?
- Nobody likes me.

78
00:05:24.324 --> 00:05:26.725
Well. you're
inconsistent and extreme.

79
00:05:27.127 --> 00:05:28.993
People don't know
how to respond to you.

80
00:05:29.162 --> 00:05:31.393
- I was joking.
- Sorry.

81
00:05:31.598 --> 00:05:34.193
Bring our suspect for
questioning. I wanna talk to him.

82
00:05:34.367 --> 00:05:38.463
Ahem. no can do. Donovan's
gonna do it. He insisted.

83
00:05:38.805 --> 00:05:40.398
Great.

84
00:05:42.609 --> 00:05:45.169
I didn't realize there
were so many people.

85
00:05:45.612 --> 00:05:48.810
I've been cooped
up at the farmhouse.

86
00:05:48.982 --> 00:05:51.247
I wanted Joey to be comfortable.

87
00:05:52.853 --> 00:05:55.322
I know he trusts you. This
would have overwhelmed him.

88
00:05:55.488 --> 00:05:57.081
Hmm.

89
00:06:00.527 --> 00:06:04.487
- Any word from Jacob and Paul?
- No.

90
00:06:05.265 --> 00:06:09.066
They haven't called and
there's been nothing on the news.

91
00:06:09.236 --> 00:06:13.332
Well. we'll take that as a good
sign that they're somewhere safe.

92
00:06:17.377 --> 00:06:21.747
You know. I will never forget
what you've done for me.

93
00:06:21.948 --> 00:06:24.247
I have my son because of you.

94
00:06:27.454 --> 00:06:28.547
What the...?

95
00:06:35.428 --> 00:06:37.090
Joe Carroll.

96
00:06:42.235 --> 00:06:43.396
How the hell are you?

97
00:06:47.674 --> 00:06:49.802
- Roderick!
- Heh.

98
00:06:49.976 --> 00:06:52.207
Ah. I got here as
soon as I could.

99
00:06:53.480 --> 00:06:54.709
It is good to see you.

100
00:06:57.484 --> 00:07:01.615
- I'm Roderick. You must be Emma.
- Nice to meet you in person. ha. ha.

101
00:07:01.788 --> 00:07:03.188
- Darling.
- Easy on the charm. huh?

102
00:07:05.959 --> 00:07:08.952
So far everything has
worked out as planned.

103
00:07:09.195 --> 00:07:11.426
Sure. there's been a few
hiccups along the way.

104
00:07:11.598 --> 00:07:14.966
Ryan Hardy has
kept us on our toes.

105
00:07:15.201 --> 00:07:17.466
But you've
improvised quite nicely.

106
00:07:17.637 --> 00:07:20.197
I'm in your debt. my
friend. Thank you.

107
00:07:21.474 --> 00:07:23.443
I'm the one that owes you.

108
00:07:26.613 --> 00:07:28.605
I killed two of those girls.

109
00:07:31.851 --> 00:07:33.945
You took the blame.

110
00:07:34.154 --> 00:07:37.522
There's no point in both
of us rotting away in here.

111
00:07:38.825 --> 00:07:40.657
How can I ever repay you?

112
00:07:41.094 --> 00:07:45.964
Oh. you will. My
friend. you will.

113
00:07:48.969 --> 00:07:52.167
We're in this
together. you and me.

114
00:07:52.372 --> 00:07:55.433
Everything I am
is because of you.

115
00:08:02.248 --> 00:08:04.945
Come on. I'll show you around.

116
00:08:05.685 --> 00:08:08.052
Is this place insane or what?

117
00:08:09.255 --> 00:08:10.416
Interesting.

118
00:08:11.858 --> 00:08:13.156
It's a work in progress.

119
00:08:14.260 --> 00:08:15.853
We're slowly fixing it up.

120
00:08:16.029 --> 00:08:17.657
- It takes a village. right?
- Huh? Heh.

121
00:08:17.864 --> 00:08:19.492
WOMAN: <i>Sheriff Nelson?</i>

122
00:08:19.666 --> 00:08:20.690
Yeah. Sheriff here.

123
00:08:20.867 --> 00:08:24.326
<i>Did you want potato salad or
coleslaw with your sandwich?</i>

124
00:08:24.504 --> 00:08:27.167
Let's go with potato
salad today. Sally honey.

125
00:08:27.340 --> 00:08:29.832
<i>- Roger that. sir.</i>
- Thank you.

126
00:08:32.979 --> 00:08:35.642
Sheriff's a very
important job around here.

127
00:08:40.153 --> 00:08:42.486
It seems our man in
custody has shut down.

128
00:08:42.856 --> 00:08:44.916
He won't talk to anyone but you.

129
00:08:45.091 --> 00:08:46.354
Oh.

130
00:08:47.727 --> 00:08:49.719
What would you
like me to do. sir?

131
00:08:51.664 --> 00:08:55.999
I'd like you to sit in with me.
And you can call me Nick.

132
00:08:56.202 --> 00:08:59.297
Sure thing. Nick.
Anything I can do to help.

133
00:09:17.857 --> 00:09:20.224
I'm Nick Donovan. And you are?

134
00:09:22.562 --> 00:09:24.258
Hello. Ryan.

135
00:09:25.365 --> 00:09:29.826
Hello. How's the leg? I'm
sorry. I don't know your name.

136
00:09:30.570 --> 00:09:31.936
You can call me David.

137
00:09:40.547 --> 00:09:42.539
This guy is nuts.

138
00:09:44.117 --> 00:09:45.210
Look at him.

139
00:09:50.657 --> 00:09:55.595
Is this a staring contest?
Because you asked to see me.

140
00:09:55.795 --> 00:09:57.423
Here I am.

141
00:09:58.264 --> 00:09:59.960
How did you like the plot twist?

142
00:10:00.433 --> 00:10:04.234
Joe Carroll escaping twice.
Bet you didn't see that coming.

143
00:10:04.404 --> 00:10:06.669
Yeah. that was good.
Now you're boring me.

144
00:10:06.973 --> 00:10:09.374
So if you've got
something to say. say it.

145
00:10:10.143 --> 00:10:13.477
Or you can tell us
where we find Joe.

146
00:10:13.947 --> 00:10:15.745
Oh. you're not gonna find Joe.

147
00:10:16.149 --> 00:10:20.416
You don't find us. We find you.

148
00:10:20.587 --> 00:10:24.388
And we're everywhere. We're
your sons. your daughters...

149
00:10:24.591 --> 00:10:27.891
<i>husbands. your
wives. neighbors...</i>

150
00:10:28.094 --> 00:10:32.088
fathers and mothers. And
soon. more will be dead tomorrow.

151
00:10:32.532 --> 00:10:35.832
Now you're paraphrasing Ted
Bundy. He's paraphrasing Ted Bundy.

152
00:10:36.035 --> 00:10:37.059
Poorly. I might add.

153
00:10:37.237 --> 00:10:38.514
<i>What is the point of this?</i>

154
00:10:38.538 --> 00:10:40.803
Hold close your fear.

155
00:10:42.509 --> 00:10:46.776
It is all that you know when
you take your last breath.

156
00:10:48.414 --> 00:10:50.007
Wow. that was creepy.

157
00:10:53.520 --> 00:10:59.357
So how about you give
us something real. David?

158
00:11:12.639 --> 00:11:13.698
- Hey.
- Hey.

159
00:11:18.478 --> 00:11:19.707
Guards!

160
00:11:21.080 --> 00:11:23.208
Guards! Guards!

161
00:11:24.484 --> 00:11:26.043
He took something.

162
00:11:41.701 --> 00:11:43.693
We have tech-town in here.
- Heh.

163
00:11:43.903 --> 00:11:46.998
Everything is completely
secure. untraceable.

164
00:11:47.974 --> 00:11:51.706
Charlie. you've been hiding
yourself away since I got here.

165
00:11:57.116 --> 00:11:58.607
I'm sorry. sir.

166
00:12:00.019 --> 00:12:02.011
About Claire. I failed you.

167
00:12:02.889 --> 00:12:05.723
- I want you to know that...
- Not now. Charlie.

168
00:12:06.559 --> 00:12:08.892
Don't be so hard
on yourself. Charlie.

169
00:12:09.095 --> 00:12:11.428
Take what you've
learned and apply it.

170
00:12:11.598 --> 00:12:13.863
- Hmm?
- Heh. Hmm.

171
00:12:15.868 --> 00:12:18.030
All right. this way.

172
00:12:18.938 --> 00:12:21.806
Hi. You remember Louise?

173
00:12:22.041 --> 00:12:25.443
- But of course. She was my savior.
- The pleasure was mine.

174
00:12:29.382 --> 00:12:31.817
We set this up for you.

175
00:12:32.118 --> 00:12:36.317
It's meant to be your...
Your inspiration room.

176
00:12:36.889 --> 00:12:41.224
Where you can write. hold
class. Poker on Mondays...

177
00:12:41.427 --> 00:12:43.794
How many people live here?

178
00:12:44.397 --> 00:12:47.765
- I see so many new faces.
- I've been recruiting.

179
00:12:47.934 --> 00:12:51.234
There's the ones you know. about
a dozen more you have yet to meet.

180
00:12:52.038 --> 00:12:53.666
We've. uh. built a life here.

181
00:12:54.173 --> 00:12:58.338
In a small town that you're a
sheriff of. heh. That's genius.

182
00:13:00.613 --> 00:13:03.981
Everybody's so excited
you're finally here. Joe.

183
00:13:04.150 --> 00:13:05.209
Hmm.

184
00:13:05.385 --> 00:13:08.844
- They're anxious to get started.
- As am I.

185
00:13:10.757 --> 00:13:13.784
Claire first. Do we
know where she is?

186
00:13:13.960 --> 00:13:17.362
She's in protective custody.
They. uh. got her out. clean.

187
00:13:17.997 --> 00:13:21.331
My son needs his mother.

188
00:13:21.501 --> 00:13:25.438
Losing Claire was a mistake.

189
00:13:25.638 --> 00:13:28.073
I'm sorry about that. Joe.

190
00:13:29.509 --> 00:13:32.001
But I have an idea
how we can find her.

191
00:13:34.380 --> 00:13:35.848
Let the FBI tell us.

192
00:13:37.950 --> 00:13:41.148
I've done all the research.
I got it all worked out.

193
00:13:44.090 --> 00:13:47.549
Which one first? Hmm?

194
00:13:50.830 --> 00:13:51.889
This one.

195
00:13:52.131 --> 00:13:54.157
We're waiting on
the coroner's report.

196
00:13:54.334 --> 00:13:58.362
But I think it's a suicide pill. a
basic cyanide or common PSP toxin.

197
00:13:58.604 --> 00:14:01.039
- He had it in his hand?
- It was sewn into his skin.

198
00:14:01.207 --> 00:14:03.836
Implanted in the fold between
his thumb and forefinger.

199
00:14:04.010 --> 00:14:07.640
It's a CIA ploy from the '60s. Al
Qaeda has been known to use it as well.

200
00:14:08.648 --> 00:14:10.139
I got some new intel
on the deceased.

201
00:14:10.316 --> 00:14:11.340
Thanks. MITCHELL: Mm-hm.

202
00:14:11.517 --> 00:14:12.985
I'll take that.

203
00:14:16.723 --> 00:14:18.487
Seriously?

204
00:14:18.858 --> 00:14:22.693
Based on his method of suicide. they
ran his prints through a military database.

205
00:14:22.862 --> 00:14:24.888
- Came up with a match.
- Got a positive ID?

206
00:14:25.064 --> 00:14:27.727
More than that. He was
named in an investigation.

207
00:14:27.900 --> 00:14:31.894
There were soldiers conducting lethal
fights with Iraqi civilians for sport.

208
00:14:34.440 --> 00:14:35.931
My email was hacked. Was it you?

209
00:14:36.509 --> 00:14:38.171
Yeah. that was me. I did it.

210
00:14:38.378 --> 00:14:41.644
Sorry. Ryan. you don't have
access to hack my email. Weston?

211
00:14:42.515 --> 00:14:45.849
Uh. yes. sir. I
did. I apologize.

212
00:14:46.052 --> 00:14:47.076
I need a word.

213
00:14:57.363 --> 00:15:00.390
- What's going on?
- I think I got Weston in trouble.

214
00:15:00.600 --> 00:15:04.093
- They hacked Donovan's email.
- You what? Damn it. Ryan.

215
00:15:04.303 --> 00:15:07.034
- What happened?
- I'm being sent home.

216
00:15:07.807 --> 00:15:08.934
Wait. wait.

217
00:15:09.175 --> 00:15:11.940
This is my fault. I'll
go. I asked him to do it.

218
00:15:12.111 --> 00:15:13.875
- He's going home.
- That's a bad call.

219
00:15:14.080 --> 00:15:15.207
Excuse me?

220
00:15:15.415 --> 00:15:18.249
We're spinning our wheels.
We need to keep things moving.

221
00:15:18.418 --> 00:15:20.410
We can't if you're
sitting on information.

222
00:15:20.620 --> 00:15:22.521
This investigation
starts at my desk now.

223
00:15:22.688 --> 00:15:24.987
I understand your
relationship to this case...

224
00:15:25.224 --> 00:15:28.626
and I'm trying hard to be polite.
but it's not something I excel at.

225
00:15:35.501 --> 00:15:37.970
Just go back to the motel...

226
00:15:38.204 --> 00:15:41.800
and we'll talk in the morning.

227
00:16:36.262 --> 00:16:40.529
- Are you getting in?
- No. thanks. I'll wait for the next one.

228
00:17:18.037 --> 00:17:19.699
- You okay?
- Yeah.

229
00:17:21.073 --> 00:17:22.803
You need some help with that?

230
00:17:25.111 --> 00:17:27.012
No. I'm fine. Thanks.

231
00:17:38.224 --> 00:17:39.902
<i>Your call has been forwarded...</i>

232
00:17:39.926 --> 00:17:40.950
<i>to an automatic voice...</i>

233
00:17:41.427 --> 00:17:43.453
Mitchell. Weston's
not picking up.

234
00:17:43.629 --> 00:17:46.292
- I tried three times.
- Not like him. He always picks up.

235
00:17:46.465 --> 00:17:49.094
- Can you ping his phone?
- Already on it.

236
00:17:51.037 --> 00:17:52.938
Says he's at the motel.

237
00:17:54.106 --> 00:17:57.941
Something's not right. I'm gonna
check it out. Let Parker know.

238
00:18:23.235 --> 00:18:25.136
You need to pace yourself.
- Heh.

239
00:18:25.371 --> 00:18:27.169
When was the last
time you were drunk?

240
00:18:27.373 --> 00:18:29.342
Oh. years.

241
00:18:31.010 --> 00:18:33.275
Oh. is that Scotch I see?

242
00:18:36.816 --> 00:18:40.412
- Oh. it's really bad Scotch.
- Heh.

243
00:18:40.586 --> 00:18:42.020
