250
00:19:04.610 --> 00:19:08.138
I'm sure there are a lot of things
that you need to catch up on.

251
00:19:09.548 --> 00:19:12.017
Yes. yes. that's...

252
00:19:12.818 --> 00:19:14.184
That is true.

253
00:19:14.353 --> 00:19:18.415
It has been depressingly
quiet on that front.

254
00:19:20.059 --> 00:19:22.358
Well. you need to fix that then.

255
00:19:24.830 --> 00:19:25.923
Here you go.

256
00:19:28.834 --> 00:19:30.632
All better?

257
00:19:32.738 --> 00:19:35.071
Yes. all better.

258
00:19:37.143 --> 00:19:40.443
Roderick called.
All is going to plan.

259
00:19:40.646 --> 00:19:44.481
- They should be back by dawn.
- Splendid. Aaron. Thank you.

260
00:19:47.887 --> 00:19:51.517
So how long have you and
Roderick known each other?

261
00:19:52.158 --> 00:19:56.687
Oh. uh. just a little bit
longer than I've known you.

262
00:19:57.463 --> 00:19:59.489
Was he a student of yours?

263
00:19:59.832 --> 00:20:05.203
Yes. in some ways he
was. um. my first student.

264
00:20:05.805 --> 00:20:07.000
<i>Why are we here?</i>

265
00:20:07.540 --> 00:20:09.338
- Why. are you scared?
- No.

266
00:20:11.177 --> 00:20:14.045
Should I be. Professor Carroll?

267
00:20:32.264 --> 00:20:34.130
So now what?

268
00:20:35.801 --> 00:20:36.996
What am I doing here?

269
00:20:39.271 --> 00:20:41.069
I'd like to teach you.

270
00:20:50.750 --> 00:20:54.881
Now. first. I like
to gauge their fear.

271
00:20:57.022 --> 00:20:58.820
Listen to their breathing.

272
00:21:01.060 --> 00:21:02.824
You want to get in sync with it.

273
00:21:05.164 --> 00:21:07.292
Make their breathing
become yours.

274
00:21:07.733 --> 00:21:11.829
It's a way to connect
to their heartbeat.

275
00:21:19.311 --> 00:21:22.475
First. take the very
tip of the blade.

276
00:21:22.681 --> 00:21:25.446
And you place it
softly on their skin...

277
00:21:25.651 --> 00:21:27.347
and push...

278
00:21:27.586 --> 00:21:29.612
ever so gently.
until you feel...

279
00:21:30.256 --> 00:21:32.953
the moment of...

280
00:21:36.996 --> 00:21:38.555
give.

281
00:21:46.772 --> 00:21:48.365
Your Scotch. heh.

282
00:21:49.341 --> 00:21:52.175
- Oh.
- Your Scotch is all. heh...

283
00:21:55.214 --> 00:21:56.341
Joe.

284
00:22:03.956 --> 00:22:05.652
I love...

285
00:22:05.825 --> 00:22:08.989
I love my wife. Emma.

286
00:22:12.698 --> 00:22:15.031
You understand that?

287
00:22:16.402 --> 00:22:20.601
Now. let's go and
find the others. um...

288
00:23:12.958 --> 00:23:15.553
Hey. Did Mitchell send the
motel surveillance footage?

289
00:23:15.928 --> 00:23:17.396
Yeah. got it right here.

290
00:23:17.563 --> 00:23:20.727
They could have killed him. but
they didn't. They want something.

291
00:23:21.433 --> 00:23:23.766
Confirmed identities of
who we're dealing with.

292
00:23:23.969 --> 00:23:26.598
Charles Mead. man who
abducted Claire Matthews. is one.

293
00:23:26.772 --> 00:23:29.401
The other is Louise
Sinclair. out of New Orleans.

294
00:23:29.675 --> 00:23:32.235
- Former Black water operative.
- Another overachiever.

295
00:23:32.411 --> 00:23:34.107
Find out if she
ran the plates yet.

296
00:23:34.313 --> 00:23:36.805
We put out an APB in the
300-mile radius of Richmond.

297
00:23:36.982 --> 00:23:39.952
- If it's out there. we'll find it.
- Put the call on speaker.

298
00:23:41.320 --> 00:23:45.189
Debra? It's Nick. The image
of the license plate isn't perfect.

299
00:23:45.391 --> 00:23:48.122
We can make out three.
maybe four numbers. clearly.

300
00:23:48.727 --> 00:23:52.562
But local police found nine potential
matches of the color. make. and model.

301
00:23:52.731 --> 00:23:54.597
They got nine
matches on the plates.

302
00:23:54.800 --> 00:23:55.824
Uh. where are the cars?

303
00:23:56.001 --> 00:23:58.246
<i>A couple are registered
to upstate New York.</i>

304
00:23:58.270 --> 00:24:01.297
- Two registered in upstate New York...
- Two are out of service.

305
00:24:01.473 --> 00:24:04.773
Police spotted one outside an
abandoned shipyard in Newport Harbor.

306
00:24:04.944 --> 00:24:08.813
Police spotted one outside an
abandoned shipyard in Newport Harbor.

307
00:24:08.981 --> 00:24:10.609
- That's the one.
- How do you know?

308
00:24:10.783 --> 00:24:14.982
Time on the video is half an hour ago.
how long it takes to get to Newport Harbor.

309
00:24:15.154 --> 00:24:18.124
Plus. they need someplace
quiet to do what they're gonna do.

310
00:24:18.290 --> 00:24:19.918
<i>Abandoned
shipyard fits the bill.</i>

311
00:24:20.092 --> 00:24:21.116
Sounds like a hunch.

312
00:24:21.293 --> 00:24:23.524
- A good one. We're heading over.
- That's my call.

313
00:24:23.762 --> 00:24:25.628
So make it.

314
00:24:28.033 --> 00:24:29.626
Fine. Go.

315
00:24:30.536 --> 00:24:32.232
Let's go.

316
00:24:43.983 --> 00:24:45.542
Agent Weston.

317
00:24:47.052 --> 00:24:50.853
Welcome to our
little slice of paradise.

318
00:24:51.056 --> 00:24:53.287
Thanks. And you are?

319
00:24:53.859 --> 00:24:56.522
I'm your host for
tonight's main event.

320
00:24:57.830 --> 00:24:59.526
Here's how it works.

321
00:24:59.698 --> 00:25:01.690
I'm going to ask
you a few questions...

322
00:25:01.867 --> 00:25:04.837
and you're going to
answer them truthfully.

323
00:25:06.705 --> 00:25:08.469
And if I don't?

324
00:25:08.640 --> 00:25:10.666
That's where it gets fun. - Heh.

325
00:25:10.843 --> 00:25:13.904
You see. we have a little game
we like to play. a fight sport.

326
00:25:15.280 --> 00:25:18.011
You lie. we begin a round.

327
00:25:19.385 --> 00:25:21.411
You lie some more...

328
00:25:23.389 --> 00:25:24.687
it gets worse. heh.

329
00:25:28.727 --> 00:25:30.252
So.

330
00:25:30.429 --> 00:25:32.057
Tell me.

331
00:25:35.834 --> 00:25:37.325
Where is Claire Matthews?

332
00:25:41.573 --> 00:25:43.439
Is that what this is about?

333
00:25:43.609 --> 00:25:47.979
Sorry. man. She's in protective
custody. No one knows where she is.

334
00:25:49.748 --> 00:25:51.239
That's a lie.

335
00:25:52.418 --> 00:25:54.114
Round one.

336
00:25:56.188 --> 00:25:57.884
Ding. ding.

337
00:26:05.464 --> 00:26:07.433
Come on. now. you need to get up.
- Ugh.

338
00:26:07.599 --> 00:26:09.359
Big boy. we're
gonna have some fun.

339
00:26:14.139 --> 00:26:15.402
Nice!

340
00:26:17.676 --> 00:26:19.338
Match on our hands here.

341
00:26:19.511 --> 00:26:22.879
Rah-rah. Pick it up. boys.
Let's see some real blood.

342
00:26:47.573 --> 00:26:49.371
Okay. All right. all right.

343
00:26:54.213 --> 00:26:55.909
Wanna end this?

344
00:26:56.615 --> 00:26:57.742
Tell us where Claire is.

345
00:27:01.086 --> 00:27:02.145
I don't know anything.

346
00:27:03.422 --> 00:27:05.516
You think we don't
know about you.

347
00:27:06.625 --> 00:27:09.026
Agent Michael Emerson Weston.

348
00:27:09.194 --> 00:27:13.632
Born in San Diego. California.
Political Science major at Wesleyan.

349
00:27:13.999 --> 00:27:15.695
Then three years at Quantico.

350
00:27:15.934 --> 00:27:19.029
Studying high profile
personal security.

351
00:27:19.204 --> 00:27:23.539
You know everyone. you know
everything about FBI protective custody.

352
00:27:25.544 --> 00:27:27.706
You know where they hid Claire.

353
00:27:28.614 --> 00:27:33.279
You know everything about me.
And I don't know anything about you.

354
00:27:33.452 --> 00:27:34.511
Roderick?

355
00:27:38.690 --> 00:27:40.818
Isn't that what they call you?

356
00:27:47.499 --> 00:27:49.024
Yeah.

357
00:27:50.536 --> 00:27:53.836
Same question. second
round. Where's Claire?

358
00:27:54.006 --> 00:27:57.135
I don't know. They didn't
tell me that. Why would they?

359
00:27:57.309 --> 00:27:59.005
Round two is gonna hurt.

360
00:28:10.222 --> 00:28:11.952
Ding. ding.

361
00:28:42.387 --> 00:28:43.980
That's definitely the car.

362
00:28:44.189 --> 00:28:45.350
They gotta be inside.

363
00:28:45.524 --> 00:28:47.823
I'll check the perimeter.

364
00:28:55.601 --> 00:28:58.901
Come on. Come
on. ring-a-ding-ding.

365
00:29:01.540 --> 00:29:05.409
It's not over until
you stop breathing.

366
00:29:12.918 --> 00:29:14.614
You're still breathing.

367
00:29:17.055 --> 00:29:18.921
You got one last chance here.

368
00:29:21.927 --> 00:29:23.793
Where's Claire?

369
00:29:27.766 --> 00:29:29.598
I don't know.

370
00:29:31.270 --> 00:29:33.034
I don't... I don't know.

371
00:29:38.310 --> 00:29:40.745
- I don't know.
- I believe you.

372
00:29:41.747 --> 00:29:43.443
I believe you.

373
00:29:48.253 --> 00:29:49.949
Final round.

374
00:30:17.883 --> 00:30:18.976
Help him up.

375
00:30:22.487 --> 00:30:23.978
Get off!

376
00:30:26.024 --> 00:30:28.224
I'm going to find Claire.
whether you'll help me or not.

377
00:31:12.170 --> 00:31:13.900
I got this.

378
00:31:17.342 --> 00:31:19.208
Help me hold his head.

379
00:31:32.457 --> 00:31:34.255
Let's get out of here.

380
00:31:49.441 --> 00:31:50.465
Stop!

381
00:31:50.675 --> 00:31:51.768
FBI!

382
00:31:52.544 --> 00:31:53.910
FBI!

383
00:32:04.790 --> 00:32:06.053
Don't move. don't move.

384
00:32:06.591 --> 00:32:10.221
Ambulance is
coming. Take it easy.

385
00:32:11.830 --> 00:32:13.059
I didn't tell them. Ryan.

386
00:32:14.699 --> 00:32:16.964
I didn't tell them anything.

387
00:32:18.804 --> 00:32:20.295
Okay.

388
00:32:23.809 --> 00:32:24.970
Hey. hey. hey.

389
00:32:26.211 --> 00:32:29.272
Come on. come on.
Stay with me. buddy.

390
00:32:44.796 --> 00:32:47.493
Severe concussion. blood loss.

391
00:32:47.799 --> 00:32:50.963
He'll need surgery. but the
paramedics believe he'll pull through.

392
00:32:59.444 --> 00:33:01.140
You okay?

393
00:33:03.782 --> 00:33:04.841
No.

394
00:33:06.618 --> 00:33:10.111
I'm gonna. uh. head
over to the hospital.

395
00:33:10.288 --> 00:33:12.314
He'll be in surgery for hours.

396
00:33:13.492 --> 00:33:15.017
Still.

397
00:33:17.496 --> 00:33:20.523
You know this wasn't
your fault. Ryan?

398
00:33:22.300 --> 00:33:25.293
You can't own everything
that goes wrong.

399
00:33:26.638 --> 00:33:28.368
No. that's not it.

400
00:33:29.474 --> 00:33:32.103
It's just I know
hospitals. They're no fun.

401
00:33:32.277 --> 00:33:35.509
I just think somebody should be
there when he wakes up. that's all.

402
00:34:07.178 --> 00:34:08.578
We got nothing.

403
00:34:09.514 --> 00:34:11.540
We lost five men.

404
00:34:15.520 --> 00:34:17.011
I'm sorry. Joe.

405
00:34:20.825 --> 00:34:22.691
You'll find Claire.

406
00:34:26.865 --> 00:34:31.394
And bring her home.
Of that. I'm certain.

407
00:34:31.603 --> 00:34:33.572
I will find her.

408
00:34:35.407 --> 00:34:36.932
I owe you. man.

409
00:34:43.715 --> 00:34:45.206
One more thing.

410
00:34:59.130 --> 00:35:00.689
I've let you down again. sir.

411
00:35:00.899 --> 00:35:05.860
I won't lie. Charlie.
I'm disappointed.

412
00:35:07.539 --> 00:35:09.371
I want to make it right.

413
00:35:10.275 --> 00:35:15.441
The reason I wanted to
know you. to be a part of this...

414
00:35:16.615 --> 00:35:20.711
is I wanted my life
to mean something.

415
00:35:21.252 --> 00:35:23.221
Hmm.

416
00:36:19.944 --> 00:36:22.175
You want to do this for me?

417
00:36:22.414 --> 00:36:24.815
I want to be important. sir.

418
00:36:26.985 --> 00:36:28.817
I want my life to matter.

419
00:36:31.456 --> 00:36:33.357
This is my gift...

420
00:36:36.227 --> 00:36:38.128
and my apology.

421
00:36:57.582 --> 00:36:59.744
You will always matter.

422
00:38:54.332 --> 00:38:56.597
- How long has he been out?
- About an hour.

423
00:38:56.768 --> 00:38:57.997
His surgery went well.

424
00:38:58.303 --> 00:39:00.932
He kept saying. "I
didn't tell them anything."

425
00:39:01.105 --> 00:39:02.835
What was he talking about?

426
00:39:03.208 --> 00:39:04.676
Claire's location.

427
00:39:08.813 --> 00:39:11.840
- He knew the whole time?
- Yeah.

428
00:39:12.450 --> 00:39:16.148
He spent two years with the
protective custody division in Quantico.

429
00:39:16.654 --> 00:39:18.782
He has clearance.

430
00:39:20.091 --> 00:39:22.356
He's the only one who
does know where Claire is.

431
00:39:31.035 --> 00:39:33.368
We'll bury him in the morning.

432
00:39:35.340 --> 00:39:38.833
Oh. no. I've seen this
look. What's wrong?

433
00:39:40.411 --> 00:39:42.141
You want a drink?

434
00:39:46.351 --> 00:39:49.879
You wanna go upstairs...

435
00:39:50.054 --> 00:39:52.683
- and break a headboard again?
- Not tonight.

436
00:39:55.627 --> 00:39:58.563
- You're in a mood.
- Things are different.

437
00:39:59.430 --> 00:40:03.993
- That's all. With Joe here.
- They're supposed to be.

438
00:40:05.136 --> 00:40:07.264
This is what we've
been working towards.

439
00:40:15.947 --> 00:40:18.212
I'm sorry about Charlie too.

440
00:40:19.183 --> 00:40:22.585
I mean. well. not really. heh.

441
00:40:30.662 --> 00:40:33.393
Clean towels. Clothes.

442
00:40:38.736 --> 00:40:40.864
If these don't
fit. there's more.

443
00:40:49.113 --> 00:40:50.274
Did it help?

444
00:40:54.218 --> 00:40:58.588
I don't know if it helped
but it was certainly a rush.

445
00:41:12.303 --> 00:41:15.831
- I love my wife.
- She's not here.

446
00:41:25.283 --> 00:41:27.514
What can I do...

447
00:41:28.853 --> 00:41:32.620
to make you feel better?

448
00:42:11.162 --> 00:42:14.860
- Dick!
- Don't be like that. huh?
